Total uncertainty. The errors given for the
cross sections include:
uncertainties of the mass and thickness of
the target foil which are commonly less than 1%.
The additional error due to uncertainties of
the measurements of the monitoring radionuclides,
Na-22 and Zn-65,can be regarded to be about 2%.
The noble gas concentrations were reproducible
within 2%  and
the absolute gas amounts are accurate within 5%
Fluctuations in the beam intensity during the
irradiation were taken into account when calculating
flux densities and cross sections and they resulted
in an overall error of less than 1% for the product
nuclides presented here.
.The Uncertainty is Reported by Authors.
All considered errors added up quadratically
to the uncertainties given in tables.
* The error resulting from recoil and cross
contamination cancel out when analyzing the foils in
the middle of each target element unit.
* The error of the cross sections used for beam
monitoring were not taken into account when calculating
the uncertainties of the final results.
